    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-05-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="266"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d266">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">May</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-05-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 21, 1897</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>By note dated 18th and received yesterday afternoon, British ambassador states
                    readiness of British Government to renew arrangement of ‘94 for putting firearms
                    under seal at request of masters, but that it can not agree to proposal to
                    examine skins on landing. Copy mailed you to-day. Advise Foster as soon as he
                    lands, so that he may wait at London until copy arrives.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sherman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
